PURPOSE:

This small program uses the GCE (Google Compute Engine) API to validate that preemptive instances are running.


SETUP:

git clone git@github.com:nkelling/GCEApp.git

Create a virtualenv with Python 2.7.x
    Ubuntu: virtualenv -p <python exe> <directory>
    Mac: pyenv virtualenv <directory>

Activate the virtualenv:
    source <virtualenv dir>/bin/activate

Pip install the Google API Python client package
    pip install google-api-python-client

Create Google service account keys for your account default SA
    https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/creating-managing-service-account-keys

Download the .json file and store it under the keys/ directory

Edit main.py to create your GceApp account objects *examples provided*
